+## Live runtime certification
+
+- Use the registered `live-runtime-certification` workflow and P48 when end-to-end runtime proof is requested.
+- A plan, dry run, static test, CI pass, spawn, process exit, simulation, or disposable harness is not a live certificate.
+- The real provider-backed route must perform the bounded repository action, run validators, create a commit ahead of the recorded floor, and write the registered certification report.
+- Authentication, quota, network, unsupported adapter, dirty target, failed action, validation failure, or missing commit is an exact blocker.
